# External `DESIGN.md` and non-fleet branding

**Default fleet UI** is covered by **`DESIGN.md`** (repo root) and **`.cursor/rules/follow-devscrolls-ui-foundation.mdc`**. Use that path for normal shipping.

When the task is **explicitly** a **different** brand, **white-label**, **client design system**, or **importing a Stitch-style `DESIGN.md`** from [awesome-design-md](https://github.com/VoltAgent/awesome-design-md) (not the Devscrolls house style):

1. Read **`docs/design-md-for-agents.md`** in this package.
2. Read **`patterns/goldpath/design-md-brand-ui.md`** for the checklist (copy or author `DESIGN.md`, map tokens to CSS/Tailwind).

Do not invent full palettes and type hierarchies from memory when the user expects reference-based or industry-aligned UI; follow the digest’s links and copy a `DESIGN.md` into the project when appropriate, and resolve conflicts with the fleet foundation explicitly.
